[vee] Controlling line breaks

--

I don't know why I didn't think of this before, but controlling line breaks (at least with groff) is as easy as knowing the syntax!

Placing "'nf" above a line says, "don't break the following text". To re-enable regular line breaks, use the "'fi" command before the text you want to start breaking.

Here is the link (brought to you thanks to the 'nf control):

'nf
